Lamborghini has revealed the Huracán Performante Spyder at the Geneva Motor Show. The new Huracán features awesome specifications, including: Lamborghini said the Huracán Performante Spyder “puts the driver even closer to asphalt and air”. The new version is also 35kg lighter than the standard model, thanks to the use of new carbon fibre technology. Its makers said the convertible features an enhanced suspension system, recalibrated ESC, more responsive Lamborghini Dynamic Steering, permanent four-wheel drive, and revised ANIMA – Lamborghini’s driver-mode system. The starting price for the Huracán Performante Spyder is $308,859, excluding taxes. “The first customers will take delivery in summer 2018,” said Lamborghini.    